The van der Waals equation  

\[
\Bigl(P+\frac{a n^{2}}{V^{2}}\Bigr)(V-nb)=nRT
\]

is used with the data given.

**1. Convert the volume to the units of \(a\) and \(b\).**  

\[
V = 1.000\;\text{m}^{3}=1000\;\text{dm}^{3}
\]

**2. Number of moles of nitrogen.**  

Molar mass of \(\mathrm{N_2}\): \(M\approx 28.0\;\text{g mol}^{-1}\)

\[
n=\frac{92.4\;\text{kg}}{28.0\;\text{g mol}^{-1}}
   =\frac{92\,400\;\text{g}}{28\;\text{g mol}^{-1}}
   =3.30\times10^{3}\;\text{mol}
\]

**3. Ideal‑gas constant in the required units.**  

\[
R = 0.082057\;\text{atm·dm}^{3}\text{ mol}^{-1}\text{ K}^{-1}
\]

**4. Compute the terms of the equation.**

\[
nRT = (3.30\times10^{3})(0.082057)(500\;\text{K})
      =1.3539\times10^{5}\;\text{atm·dm}^{3}
\]

\[
V-nb = 1000\;\text{dm}^{3} - (3.30\times10^{3})(0.0387\;\text{dm}^{3}\text{ mol}^{-1})
      =1000 - 127.71 = 872.29\;\text{dm}^{3}
\]

\[
\frac{a n^{2}}{V^{2}} = 
\frac{1.352\;\text{atm·dm}^{6}\text{ mol}^{-2}\;(3.30\times10^{3})^{2}}
     {(1000\;\text{dm}^{3})^{2}}
 = 1.352\frac{10.89\times10^{6}}{10^{6}}
 = 14.72\;\text{atm}
\]

**5. Solve for \(P\).**

\[
P + 14.72 = \frac{nRT}{V-nb}
