#### 0.139

The vibrational frequency of a diatomic molecule in the harmonic‑oscillator approximation is  

\[
\nu = \frac{1}{2\pi}\sqrt{\frac{k}{\mu}}
\]

where  

* \(k\) = force constant (N m\(^{-1}\))  
* \(\mu\) = reduced mass of the two atoms (kg)  

The wavenumber \(\tilde{\nu}\) (in cm\(^{-1}\)) is obtained from  

\[
\tilde{\nu}= \frac{\nu}{c}
\]

with \(c = 2.9979\times10^{10}\,\text{cm s}^{-1}\).

---

### 1. Reduced mass of \({}^{35}\text{Cl}_2\)

Atomic mass of \({}^{35}\text{Cl}\) ≈ 34.96885 u  

\(1\;\text{u}=1.660539\times10^{-27}\,\text{kg}\)

\[
m_{\text{Cl}} = 34.96885\;\text{u}\times 1.660539\times10^{-27}\,\frac{\text{kg}}{\text{u}}
           \approx 5.807\times10^{-26}\,\text{kg}
\]

For two identical atoms  

\[
\mu = \frac{m_{\text{Cl}}}{2}
    \approx \frac{5.807\times10^{-26}}{2}
    = 2.903\times10^{-26}\,\text{kg}
\]

---

### 2. Harmonic‑oscillator frequency (Hz)

\[
\frac{k}{\mu}= \frac{319\;\text{N m}^{-1}}{2.903\times10^{-26}\,\text{kg}}
            \approx 1.10\times10^{28}\,\text{s}^{-2}
\]

\[
\sqrt{\frac{k}{\mu}} \approx \sqrt{1.10\times10^{28}}
                     = 1.05\times10^{14}\,\text{s}^{-1}
\]

\[
\nu = \frac{1}{2\pi}\sqrt{\frac{k}{\mu}}
    = \frac{1.05\times10^{14}}{2\pi}
    \approx 1.67\times10^{13}\,\text{Hz}
\]

---

### 3. Convert to wavenumber (cm\(^{-1}\))

\[
\tilde{\nu}= \frac{\nu}{c}
           = \frac{1.67\times10^{13}\,\text{s}^{-1}}
                  {2.998\times10^{10}\,\text{cm s}^{-1}}
           \approx 5.56\times10^{2}\,\text{cm}^{-1}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{\tilde{\nu}\;\approx\;5.6\times10^{2}\ \text{cm}^{-1}}
\]

Thus the fundamental vibrational frequency of \({}^{35}\text{Cl}^{35}\text{Cl}\) is about **\(5.6\times10^{2}\,\text{cm}^{-1}\)**.  

#### 556.5 for your final answer.

The expression  

\[
\beta = 2\pi c \,\tilde{\omega}_{\text{obs}}\,
\sqrt{\frac{\mu}{2D}}
\]

requires the reduced mass \(\mu\) of HCl and the dissociation energy per molecule \(D\).

---

### 1. Reduced mass \(\mu\)

\[
\begin{aligned}
m_{\mathrm H} &= 1.007825\;\text{u},\\
m_{\;^{35}\mathrm{Cl}} &= 34.968852\;\text{u},\\[2mm]
\mu &= \frac{m_{\mathrm H}\,m_{\;^{35}\mathrm{Cl}}}
           {m_{\mathrm H}+m_{\;^{35}\mathrm{Cl}}}
      =\frac{1.007825\times34.968852}
            {1.007825+34.968852}\;\text{u}\\
    &= 1.626\times10^{-27}\;\text{kg}
\end{aligned}
\]
(using \(1\;\text{u}=1.660539\times10^{-27}\,\text{kg}\)).

---

### 2. Dissociation energy per molecule  

\[
\begin{aligned}
D_{\text{mol}} &= 440.2\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}=4.402\times10^{5}\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\\
D &= \frac{D_{\text{mol}}}{N_{\!A}}
   =\frac{4.402\times10^{5}}{6.02214076\times10^{23}}
   =7.312\times10^{-19}\;\text{J}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3. Frequency term \(c\tilde{\omega}_{\text{obs}}\)

\[
\tilde{\omega}_{\text{obs}} = 2886\;\text{cm}^{-1},\qquad
c = 2.99792458\times10^{10}\;\text{cm s}^{-1}
\]

\[
c\tilde{\omega}_{\text{obs}} = (2.9979\times10^{10})(2886)
                              = 8.65\times10^{13}\;\text{s}^{-1}
\]

---

### 4. The square‑root factor  

\[
\sqrt{\frac{\mu}{2D}}=
\sqrt{\frac{1.626\times10^{-27}}{2(7.312\times10^{-19})}}
= \sqrt{1.112\times10^{-9}}
= 3.334\times10^{-5}\;\text{s m}^{-1}
\]

---

### 5. Assemble \(\beta\)

\[
\begin{aligned}
\beta &= 2\pi\,(c\tilde{\omega}_{\text{obs}})\,
        \sqrt{\frac{\mu}{2D}}\\[2mm]
     &= 2\pi\,(8.65\times10^{13})\,
        (3.334\times10^{-5})\\[2mm]
     &= 5.435\times10^{14}\times3.334\times10^{-5}\\[2mm]
     &= 1.81\times10^{10}\;\text{m}^{-1}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{\beta \approx 1.81\times10^{10}\ \text{m}^{-1}}
\]

In the requested units of \(10^{10}\,\text{m}^{-1}\),

\[
\beta \;\approx\; \mathbf{1.81}
\]

