\]

Calculate \(h c \tilde{\omega}_{e}\) (per molecule)  

\[
\begin{aligned}
h c \tilde{\omega}_{e} &= (6.62607015\times10^{-34}\,\text{J·s})
                         (2.99792458\times10^{10}\,\text{cm s}^{-1})
                         (2886\;\text{cm}^{-1})\\
&= 5.73\times10^{-20}\;\text{J}
\end{aligned}
\]

Convert to per‑mole energy  

\[
h c \tilde{\omega}_{e}\;( \text{per mol}) = 
5.73\times10^{-20}\,\text{J}\times N_A
= 5.73\times10^{-20}\times6.02214076\times10^{23}
\approx 3.45\times10^{4}\;\text{J mol}^{-1}=34.5\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}
\]

Now  

\[
\tilde{x}_{e}= \frac{34.5\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}}{4\times 440.2\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}}
               =\frac{34.5}{1760.8}\approx 1.96\times10^{-2}
\]

\[
